Preheat the #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling
optional).

Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

When the oven is hot, cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Once cooked, toss together with the @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%grams}.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @water{2%tsp}
and @salt{1/4%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Add the @Irish beef mince{250%grams}, season with @pepper{} and mix everything
together with your hands.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, then form into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the burgers until browned on the outside and cooked through,
~{10-12%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins, adjusting heat as needed.

> Beef is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, transfer from pan.
> Cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry @Irish bacon{170%grams} until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.
Remove from the pan once cooked.

Return the pan to high heat, adding the @creme fraiche{125%grams} and
@beef stock{1%sachet}.

Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @truffle oil{1%pack}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cover to keep warm.

> Loosen with a splash of water if the sauce becomes too thick.

Chop the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Toss the chopped tomato together in a bowl with the @salad leaves{40%grams}, a
drizzle of @oil{to taste} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

To assemble the burgers, top each base bun with the beef burger, some bacon
strips and a spoonful of truffle sauce.

Close with the top bun.

Serve the cheesy chips and salad alongside.